OL,3,CThe 5k run in its second year helping
OL,4,Cthose who've lost
OL,6,FFor Brandon's Mum Joanne, this is the
OL,7,Fcause that keeps her going. She said,
OL,8,F"This is what gets us up in the
OL,9,Fmorning, if we can make a difference
OL,10,Fto other children grieving within the
OL,11,Fmidlands, within the schools, getting
OL,12,Fthe teachers trained on how they can
OL,13,Fsupport a child grieving within the
OL,14,Fschools, that's what our drive is now"
OL,16,FJust like last year, the race proved
OL,17,Fto be a success with over a thousand
OL,18,Fpounds raised on the day meaning that
OL,19,Fthis 5k run is keeping Brandon's
OL,20,Fmemory alive whilst also making a real
OL,21,Fdifference to those who've also lost.
